unction calculates the remaining space in each bin and prioritizes the bin with the smallest overfill.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins - item\n    priority = np.where(remaining >= 0, remaining, 0)\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 3: Worst Fit Heuristic\nThis function prioritizes the bin with the largest remaining space.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins - item\n    priority = np.where(remaining >= 0, remaining, 0)\n    return np.where(priority == 0, 1, priority)\n```\n\n### Implementation 4: Random Fit Heuristic\nThis function randomly selects a bin that can fit the item.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    can_fit = bins >= item\n    priority = np.where(can_fit, np.random.random(), 0.0)\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 5: Next Fit Heuristic\nThis function places the item in the next bin that can fit it.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    can_fit = bins >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[np.where(can_fit)[0][0]] = 1.0\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 6: Multiple Fit Heuristic\nThis function tries to place the item in multiple bins and selects the best one based on the smallest overfill.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    remaining = bins - item\n    valid = remaining >= 0\n    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)\n    priority[valid] = remaining[valid]\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 7: First Fit Decreasing Heuristic\nThis function sorts the bins in decreasing order and places the item in the first bin that can fit it.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    sorted_bins = np.sort(bins)[::-1]\n    can_fit = sorted_bins >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(sorted_bins)\n    priority[np.where(can_fit)[0][0]] = 1.0\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 8: Best Fit Decreasing Heuristic\nThis function sorts the bins in decreasing order and places the item in the bin with the smallest overfill.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    sorted_bins = np.sort(bins)[::-1]\n    remaining = sorted_bins - item\n    valid = remaining >= 0\n    priority = np.zeros_like(sorted_bins)\n    priority[valid] = remaining[valid]\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 9: Worst Fit Decreasing Heuristic\nThis function sorts the bins in decreasing order and places the item in the bin with the largest remaining space.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    sorted_bins = np.sort(bins)[::-1]\n    remaining = sorted_bins - item\n    valid = remaining >= 0\n    priority = np.zeros_like(sorted_bins)\n    priority[valid] = remaining[valid]\n    return priority\n```\n\n### Implementation 10: Random Fit Decreasing Heuristic\nThis function sorts the bins in decreasing order and randomly selects a bin that can fit the item.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    sorted_bins = np.sort(bins)[::-1]\n    can_fit = sorted_bins >= item\n    priority = np.zeros_like(sorted_bins)\n    valid_indices = np.where(can_fit)[0]\n    if valid_indices.size > 0:\n        priority[np.random.choice(valid_indices)] = 1.0\n    return priority\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.std(bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))#\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.std(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (1 - np.sum(bins, axis=tuple(range(1, bins.ndim)))) - item\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.nd