em: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.mean(bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n```\n\n### Implementation 3:\nApply multiple logarithmic operations to each bin.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.log(item + bins) + np.log(item + bins) + np.log(item + bins) + np.log(item + bins) + np.log(item + bins) + np.log(item + bins)\n```\n\n### Implementation 4:\nUse exponential and logarithmic functions with a different structure.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item) * (item - bins) + np.log(item + bins)\n```\n\n### Implementation 5:\nApply exponential and logarithmic functions in a unique combination.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item) * (item - bins) + np.log(item + bins)\n```\n\n### Implementation 6:\nUse exponential and logarithmic functions with a different arrangement.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item) * (item - bins) + np.log(item + bins)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.max(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (1 - bins) / item + np.tanh(item * bins)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item * np.max(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (1 - bins) / item + np.tanh(item * bins)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return (item + bins) * (item - bins