at, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    can_fit = bins >= item\n    suitability = (bins - item) / bins + can_fit\n    return suitability\n```\n\n### Function 7: Bin Utilization\nThis function prioritizes bins based on their current utilization relative to the item.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    can_fit = bins >= item\n    utilization = bins / item\n    utilization[~can_fit] = 0\n    return utilization\n```\n\n### Function 8: Bin Capacity Ratio\nThis function prioritizes bins based on the ratio of their capacity to the item size.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    can_fit = bins >= item\n    ratio = bins / item\n    ratio[~can_fit] = 0\n    return ratio\n```\n\n### Function 9: Bin Fit Score\nThis function calculates a fit score based on how well the bin can accommodate the item.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    can_fit = bins >= item\n    fit_score = (bins - item) / bins + can_fit\n    return fit_score\n```\n\n### Function 10: Bin Utilization Score\nThis function calculates a utilization score based on the bin's current utilization relative to the item.\n\n```python\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    can_fit = bins >= item\n    utilization_score = (bins / item) * can_fit\n    return utilization_score\n", 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.max(bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) \n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item) * (item - bins) + np.log(bins) * np.sin(item)\n', 'def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.max(bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) * 6 + np.sin(