nsformation.\n- Combine multiple operations to create complex scoring.\n- Experiment with different ways to normalize or scale the scores.\n\n### Final Note:\nThe functions need to be correct and runnable, so ensure all numpy operations are valid and the dimensions match.\n</think>\n\n### Implementation 1:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.log2(bins + 2)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) \n\n### Implementation 2:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.log2(bins + 2)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.cos(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 3:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.log2(bins + 2)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 4:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.log2(bins + 2)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 5:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.log2(bins + 2)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 6:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.log2(bins + 2)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))\n\n### Implementation 7:\ndef priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.exp(item - bins) * (item * np.log2(bins + 2)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item